and extreme mass ratios q = 0.06-0.25. This is\n$\\approx$10 times greater than that observed for solar-type MS primaries. We\ndiscuss how these new eclipsing binaries provide invaluable insights,\ndiagnostics, and challenges for the formation and evolution of stars, binaries,\nand H II regions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Oct 2014 20:00:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Jan 2015 21:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
