fficiently hot to be collisionally ionized ($T > 10^5\\,$K) and that a\nsubstantial fraction of the hot gas has a metallicity $\\gtrsim 10^{-1}$ of\nsolar. Given the high metallicity and large velocity extent (out to\n$\\sim1.5\\times v_{\\rm circ}$) of this gas, we conclude that we have detected\nhot, metal enriched outflows arising from star-forming galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Oct 2014 01:00:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 25 Apr 2015 13:16:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
